{
  "stem": "12491.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was in front of a group of people talking to us, but he never called me by name, or pointed me out, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was a-- I was a nobody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I was an electrician.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When we came to Schindler's factory there, we found out that this is a rather large complex of red brick buildings which, originally, was a Jewish factory of materials-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] what do you call materials?",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fabrics, fabrics, that's right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Fabrics and wool-- woolen things, and we have to empty that factory from these things, and prepare the site to receive the machinery which Schindler was to ship in, which he eventually did-- was-- which he eventually did.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the electrical department, of which I became an electrician, was divided into two people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The more experienced people were to work inside to wire the machinery, and the less experienced people were to work outside to build electric fence.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, of course, I was not experienced, so I was building the electric fence.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "During the months of December and January-- December '44 and January '45, I was actually working outside in snow and cold, building an electric fence.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There we were under guards of SS, and one day I managed to organize several potatoes, and I baked the potatoes just simply making fire, burying the potatoes, and burning-- and baking them on the ground.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was caught doing it, and the SS men beat me so badly that I lost my teeth, many of them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I lost my hearing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "For seven or eight days, I didn't hear at all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now I wear two hearing aids.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Eventually my hearing returned, but it was damaged.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
